-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Candente, Cementos Pacasmayo
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-04T22:03:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/peru-stocks-buenaventura-candente-rio-alto-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of the close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  fell 1.7 percent to 23,622.59. The
 MSCI (MXPECAPD)  All Peru Capped Index slid 1.7 percent to 2,980.63.  Cementos Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASI1)  (CPACASC1 PE), the Hochschild
Group’s cement producer, fell 4.3 percent to 6.40 soles after
U.S. stocks slumped, said Estefany Castillo, an analyst at
Scotiabank Peru.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural-gas
producer with operations in Peru, dropped 3.7 percent to $1.31
as crude futures declined in  New York . The government said it
won’t renew oil contracts with companies including Maple.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VCM\B)  (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver
and zinc producer, slid 3.5 percent to 3.57 soles after silver
slumped.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 2.5 percent to $39.50 after
gold declined to a 12-week low.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, dropped 2.9 percent
to $1.01 after copper declined the most this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
